God knows our frame.

00:16:12.139 --> 00:16:13.179
Aren't you thankful for that?

00:16:13.899 --> 00:16:15.019
He knows your heart.

00:16:15.019 --> 00:16:17.260
You know, the Bible tells us that the heart is deceitful

00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:20.700
and it's desperately wicked in Jeremiah 17.

00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:23.899
And then the question is this, who can know it?

00:16:25.660 --> 00:16:28.700
I, the Lord, try the rains.

00:16:28.779 --> 00:16:29.820
He tries the heart.

00:16:29.820 --> 00:16:31.260
He knows your heart.

00:16:31.260 --> 00:16:32.299
You read through the scriptures.

00:16:32.299 --> 00:16:35.500
You find that the Bible says that God, he knew their thoughts.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:36.459
Isn't that amazing?

00:16:37.179 --> 00:16:38.139
God knows us.

00:16:38.139 --> 00:16:39.339
He knows our hearts.

00:16:39.339 --> 00:16:42.700
He knows that we are, he knows our frame.

00:16:42.700 --> 00:16:47.260
He knows that we're prone to wander, that we're prone to being prideful.

00:16:47.260 --> 00:16:49.260
And we find that in the text of scripture

00:16:49.260 --> 00:16:52.700
that Paul speaks about these revelations, these visions.

00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:55.179
And so Paul was given a vision,

00:16:55.179 --> 00:16:57.660
but we find that Paul was not only given a vision,

00:16:57.660 --> 00:16:59.419
but number two, he was given a thorn.

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:02.940
He was given a thorn.

00:17:02.940 --> 00:17:05.660
I want you to think about this in comparison this morning.

00:17:07.100 --> 00:17:12.139
If you were to be the recipient of a vision of having revelation,

00:17:12.139 --> 00:17:13.899
that might cause you to be prideful.

00:17:13.899 --> 00:17:17.339
It might cause you to think highly of yourself.

00:17:17.339 --> 00:17:19.739
It may cause you to rejoice and to be thankful

00:17:19.739 --> 00:17:22.459
that you had this vision or this revelation,

00:17:23.739 --> 00:17:26.459
but a thorn, a thorn.

00:17:27.739 --> 00:17:31.100
See, oftentimes we take the same approach that the apostle Paul does

00:17:31.100 --> 00:17:34.139
in beseeching the Lord to remove the thorn.

00:17:34.139 --> 00:17:35.980
And we'll get to that in just a few moments.

00:17:36.700 --> 00:17:40.540
But I want you to focus just for a moment here this morning

00:17:40.540 --> 00:17:44.459
on this truth that Paul was given a thorn.

00:17:45.339 --> 00:17:46.059
We think about this.

00:17:46.059 --> 00:17:47.899
Notice what the Bible says in verse number six.

00:17:47.899 --> 00:17:51.100
For though I would desire to glory, I shall not be a fool,

00:17:51.100 --> 00:17:52.220
for I will say the truth.

00:17:52.940 --> 00:17:55.980
But now I forbear, lest any man should think of me above that

00:17:56.619 --> 00:18:01.019
which he seemeth me to be, or that he heareth of me.

00:18:01.019 --> 00:18:04.459
And lest I should be exalted above measure,

00:18:04.459 --> 00:18:06.700
through the abundance of the revelation,

00:18:06.700 --> 00:18:12.139
there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

00:18:13.820 --> 00:18:17.260
There was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

00:18:17.260 --> 00:18:18.139
Who gave it to him?

00:18:19.980 --> 00:18:20.299
God.

00:18:22.139 --> 00:18:23.339
Who gave him the visions?

00:18:23.980 --> 00:18:25.339
Who gave him the revelations?

00:18:26.220 --> 00:18:26.540
God.

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:28.859
But then God gave him a thorn.

00:18:30.940 --> 00:18:36.299
Sometimes our perspective in life is not really biblical.

00:18:36.859 --> 00:18:38.299
What do I mean by that?

00:18:38.299 --> 00:18:44.219
Sometimes when we see this pleasant thing, this good thing,

00:18:44.219 --> 00:18:46.700
we say, oh, God gave me this.

00:18:48.779 --> 00:18:51.419
But then we see something that from our perspective,

00:18:51.419 --> 00:18:54.219
from our vantage point is not that pleasant thing

00:18:54.219 --> 00:18:57.340
or that good thing and we are disappointed in it.

00:18:57.979 --> 00:19:03.099
We don't rejoice for the thorn like we rejoice for the visions.

00:19:03.900 --> 00:19:05.820
But I want you to understand this morning

00:19:05.820 --> 00:19:11.260
that the thorn came from God and the thorn was necessary.

00:19:11.260 --> 00:19:14.380
And the thorn is reason to rejoice.

00:19:14.380 --> 00:19:14.779
Why?

00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:18.940
Because the Bible says twice in our passage of Scripture,

00:19:18.940 --> 00:19:22.700
lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:19:22.779 --> 00:19:25.099
What happens when we get full of pride?

00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:27.979
Destroys us.

00:19:27.979 --> 00:19:29.820
Can I remind you of what the Bible says?

00:19:29.820 --> 00:19:34.219
The Bible says this, God resisteth the what?

00:19:35.179 --> 00:19:35.739
The proud.

00:19:37.580 --> 00:19:41.020
So Paul says there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

00:19:41.020 --> 00:19:41.820
Why?

00:19:41.820 --> 00:19:45.820
Lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:19:45.820 --> 00:19:51.659
And if I'm exalted above measure, if I am full of pride, God resists me.

00:19:53.419 --> 00:19:54.460
Am I telling you the truth?

00:19:56.299 --> 00:19:59.900
God hates pride.

00:19:59.900 --> 00:20:02.640
God hates pride.

00:20:02.640 --> 00:20:05.620
God resisteth the proud,

00:20:05.620 --> 00:20:07.580
and what's the rest of the verse?

00:20:07.580 --> 00:20:11.500
But giveth grace unto the humble.

00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:12.940
Amen?

00:20:12.940 --> 00:20:15.640
And we find that as we study the Word of God

00:20:15.640 --> 00:20:18.020
and we look at this passage of Scripture,

00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:19.860
we find that the Apostle Paul,

00:20:19.860 --> 00:20:21.940
he's speaking to the believers in Corinth,

00:20:21.940 --> 00:20:23.620
and he says there was given to me

00:20:23.620 --> 00:20:25.620
visions and revelations,

00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:30.060
but there was given a thorn.

00:20:30.060 --> 00:20:31.260
A thorn.

00:20:31.260 --> 00:20:33.660
Many have debated what this thorn is.

00:20:33.660 --> 00:20:35.940
Many have had their ideas

00:20:35.940 --> 00:20:38.220
and they've set forth their reasons

00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:40.460
of why they believe what they believe

00:20:40.460 --> 00:20:41.900
with regard to the thorn.

00:20:41.900 --> 00:20:43.740
We find that Paul simply says

00:20:43.740 --> 00:20:46.780
there was given to me a thorn in the flesh.

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:49.540
The messenger of Satan to buffet me

00:20:49.540 --> 00:20:53.700
lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:20:53.700 --> 00:20:55.980
Isn't it interesting in verse 7

00:20:55.980 --> 00:20:59.380
that bookends to the verse of Scripture

00:20:59.380 --> 00:21:04.620
are lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:21:04.620 --> 00:21:08.620
Do you think God wants us to stay humble?

00:21:08.620 --> 00:21:09.780
Absolutely.

00:21:09.780 --> 00:21:12.260
Did Nebuchadnezzar find that God

00:21:12.260 --> 00:21:15.100
could humble a man?

00:21:15.100 --> 00:21:17.820
He found out the hard way, did he not?

00:21:17.820 --> 00:21:20.020
And at the end of the whole situation,

00:21:20.020 --> 00:21:21.540
did Nebuchadnezzar recognize

00:21:21.540 --> 00:21:25.020
that God is able to humble?

00:21:25.020 --> 00:21:26.980
But you know what Peter tells us?

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:31.260
Humble yourselves in the sight of God.

00:21:31.260 --> 00:21:34.620
Humble yourselves in the sight of God.

00:21:34.620 --> 00:21:36.380
And there are some things that God

00:21:36.380 --> 00:21:38.620
will bring into your life and into my life

00:21:38.620 --> 00:21:40.180
to keep us humble.

00:21:40.180 --> 00:21:42.860
Just like God did here for the Apostle Paul,

00:21:42.860 --> 00:21:45.780
and the Bible says that He gave him a thorn,

00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:48.700
this experience of these visions and revelations

00:21:48.740 --> 00:21:51.180
could lead to pride, could lead to glory,

00:21:51.180 --> 00:21:54.060
but we find God in His infinite wisdom,

00:21:54.060 --> 00:21:57.620
He gave to Paul this thorn in the flesh.

00:21:58.740 --> 00:22:02.260
And Paul besought the Lord that this thing would depart

00:22:02.260 --> 00:22:05.220
and God in a single word said no,

00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:07.620
we'll look at the entirety of it in just a moment,

00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:12.380
but we find that God knows best.

00:22:12.380 --> 00:22:14.100
God knows what you need.

00:22:14.100 --> 00:22:15.700
He knows what I need.

00:22:15.700 --> 00:22:18.100
He knows what will happen in our lives

00:22:18.100 --> 00:22:19.620
given certain circumstances

00:22:19.620 --> 00:22:24.620
and how we might be led to not trust Him like we should.

00:22:26.180 --> 00:22:27.900
That we'll come to a place where we begin

00:22:27.900 --> 00:22:32.260
to lean on our own understanding like we should not.

00:22:32.260 --> 00:22:33.740
Right, you understand what I'm saying?

00:22:33.740 --> 00:22:36.740
And God will allow things in our lives.

00:22:36.740 --> 00:22:40.060
God will allow things to cause us to come to a place,

00:22:40.060 --> 00:22:43.300
listen, to depend on Him.

00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:45.140
Have you ever been in a place

00:22:45.140 --> 00:22:46.820
where you just didn't know what to do?

00:22:48.140 --> 00:22:50.780
I was having discipleship and training

00:22:50.780 --> 00:22:53.580
with Fernando last week and he asked me a question.

00:22:53.580 --> 00:22:55.340
He said, have you ever felt like it's hard?

00:22:55.340 --> 00:22:56.180
Have you ever felt like you don't know what to do?

00:22:56.180 --> 00:22:59.700
And I said, Fernando, listen, let me just tell you,

00:22:59.700 --> 00:23:02.180
there's plenty of times that you see it's hard

00:23:02.180 --> 00:23:04.100
and you don't know what to do

00:23:04.100 --> 00:23:06.620
and it's not just at the beginning,

00:23:06.620 --> 00:23:08.940
it's throughout the life and ministry

00:23:08.940 --> 00:23:11.420
of a follower of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:23:11.420 --> 00:23:14.060
And we find that what is God doing in those moments?

00:23:14.060 --> 00:23:16.500
He's leading us to a place of dependence,

00:23:17.340 --> 00:23:21.580
depending upon Him, seeking Him for direction,

00:23:21.580 --> 00:23:25.420
seeking Him for what is next.

00:23:25.420 --> 00:23:28.580
And we find that as you study through the Psalms

00:23:28.580 --> 00:23:30.780
and we have on Wednesday nights here,

00:23:30.780 --> 00:23:33.900
the last several weeks that David was in a place

00:23:33.900 --> 00:23:36.700
where he needed direction and he sought the Lord.

00:23:36.700 --> 00:23:38.500
There were some circumstances in his life

00:23:38.500 --> 00:23:41.240
that brought him to that place of dependence.

00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:44.420
We see that the purpose is given to us

00:23:44.420 --> 00:23:46.780
in verse number seven as bookends to the verse

00:23:46.780 --> 00:23:49.380
that lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:23:49.380 --> 00:23:52.420
But I want you to understand that as we look at this thorn

00:23:52.420 --> 00:23:56.900
that Paul received, that this result of this thorn

00:23:56.900 --> 00:24:00.380
would bring humility and dependence.

00:24:00.380 --> 00:24:04.220
Can I tell you this morning that we need both?

00:24:05.540 --> 00:24:06.580
We need both.

00:24:07.640 --> 00:24:08.820
We need to be humble.

00:24:11.020 --> 00:24:12.900
We need to be dependent upon the Lord.

00:24:13.780 --> 00:24:15.660
Sometimes what happens, Brother Mike and I

00:24:15.660 --> 00:24:18.780
were talking last night, and as we were talking

00:24:18.780 --> 00:24:21.740
after we had dinner and the kids were playing

00:24:21.740 --> 00:24:24.660
and his son wanted to beat everybody at UNO

00:24:24.660 --> 00:24:26.940
and we were just kind of talking for a few minutes

00:24:26.940 --> 00:24:30.380
before we got into the UNO game and we began to talk

00:24:30.380 --> 00:24:32.940
about preparing messages and that sort of thing.

00:24:32.940 --> 00:24:35.660
And I said this to him.

00:24:35.660 --> 00:24:39.560
I said, you know, the message is important,

00:24:40.560 --> 00:24:44.180
but the man is of greater importance, the vessel.

00:24:45.320 --> 00:24:46.160
The vessel.

00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:50.600
And sometimes what can happen is we can get so professional

00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:54.720
and so methodical in the Christian life

00:24:56.180 --> 00:24:57.680
that we just figure out how to do it

00:24:57.680 --> 00:24:59.360
like it's a well-oiled machine.

00:25:00.280 --> 00:25:01.740
But that's not ministry.

00:25:02.600 --> 00:25:05.160
Ministry is to be lived in dependence.

00:25:05.160 --> 00:25:07.780
Your Christian life is to be lived in dependence

00:25:07.780 --> 00:25:11.060
every single day on the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:25:11.060 --> 00:25:14.560
Because when he said in John 15 that ye are the branches

00:25:14.560 --> 00:25:17.860
and I am the vine, and without me you can do nothing,

00:25:17.860 --> 00:25:20.620
he was speaking truth that was necessary

00:25:20.620 --> 00:25:23.700
for his people to understand and to accept.

00:25:24.660 --> 00:25:27.700
There are times in which we get so focused.

00:25:27.700 --> 00:25:30.420
I preached last Sunday night of too busy for Jesus

00:25:30.420 --> 00:25:33.060
and looking at Martha and that whole situation

00:25:33.060 --> 00:25:36.020
and we can just get so busy serving the master

00:25:36.060 --> 00:25:38.860
that we forget to spend time with the master.

00:25:39.700 --> 00:25:41.860
Ministry is important, serving is important,

00:25:41.860 --> 00:25:44.940
but we cannot forego, we cannot forfeit

00:25:44.940 --> 00:25:47.380
our time with Christ.

00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:51.140
So Paul was given visions, Paul was given a thorn.

00:25:51.140 --> 00:25:53.460
And let me say this as we finish up this morning,

00:25:53.460 --> 00:25:55.680
number three, Paul was given an answer.

00:25:56.780 --> 00:25:58.500
Paul was given an answer.

00:25:58.500 --> 00:25:59.940
As we look at verses eight and nine,

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:04.100
the Bible records for us this request that Paul makes

00:26:04.100 --> 00:26:05.580
and the answer that he receives.

00:26:06.180 --> 00:26:07.060
The request is simple.

00:26:07.060 --> 00:26:09.180
In verse number eight, for this thing,

00:26:09.180 --> 00:26:13.980
I besought the Lord thrice that it might depart from me.

00:26:13.980 --> 00:26:16.220
It's very plain what Paul was requesting.

00:26:16.220 --> 00:26:19.420
In fact, for some of us, we've prayed the same type

00:26:19.420 --> 00:26:21.580
of prayer that Paul has prayed.

00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:25.260
We pray in a situation, God, would you remove this?

00:26:25.260 --> 00:26:26.380
Why do we pray that way?

00:26:26.380 --> 00:26:28.100
Because we believe that he can.

00:26:30.660 --> 00:26:32.860
I believe that God can move the mountains.

00:26:32.860 --> 00:26:34.920
I believe that God can part the seas.

00:26:35.280 --> 00:26:37.360
I believe that God is still on his throne.

00:26:37.360 --> 00:26:39.800
He has all the power that he's ever had

00:26:39.800 --> 00:26:41.040
and that he ever will have.

00:26:41.040 --> 00:26:42.360
He is omnipotent.

00:26:42.360 --> 00:26:45.880
He is able to do exceeding abundantly above

00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:47.720
all that we ask or think.

00:26:48.780 --> 00:26:52.080
And I pray at times that God would remove something.

00:26:52.080 --> 00:26:52.920
Why?

00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:55.140
Because I believe that he can.

00:26:56.480 --> 00:26:58.360
And Paul besought the Lord thrice.

00:26:58.360 --> 00:27:02.120
This was not something that just one time he prayed.

00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:03.400
No, it was three times.

00:27:03.400 --> 00:27:06.520
There's an element, an aspect of maybe fervency

00:27:06.520 --> 00:27:09.700
that we could speak of here with regard to the request.

00:27:09.700 --> 00:27:12.000
And Paul sought the Lord.

00:27:13.520 --> 00:27:15.580
He knew that God was able.

00:27:15.580 --> 00:27:17.960
But we find that Paul was given an answer.

00:27:17.960 --> 00:27:20.800
Can I say it this way even before we read verse number nine?

00:27:20.800 --> 00:27:23.600
It may not always be the answer that we're looking for.

00:27:25.960 --> 00:27:28.080
I think Paul was looking for an answer

00:27:28.080 --> 00:27:30.360
that was different than the answer that he received.

00:27:30.360 --> 00:27:32.440
I think that Paul truly desired

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:36.400
that God would remove that thorn.

00:27:36.400 --> 00:27:37.600
That's why he prayed it.

00:27:40.600 --> 00:27:43.540
But God said, I'm gonna do something better.

00:27:43.540 --> 00:27:46.080
Can I tell you that his way is perfect?

00:27:46.080 --> 00:27:48.100
Can I tell you that his way is best?

00:27:49.040 --> 00:27:52.460
Can I tell you this, that his way is not always my way?

00:27:53.960 --> 00:27:55.320
His ways are not our ways.

00:27:55.320 --> 00:27:57.240
Is that not what Isaiah tells us?

00:27:57.240 --> 00:27:58.680
He transcends us.

00:27:58.680 --> 00:27:59.680
He knows better.

00:28:00.000 --> 00:28:00.840
And I was thinking this morning

00:28:00.840 --> 00:28:02.760
as I was looking at the bulletin,

00:28:02.760 --> 00:28:03.920
actually yesterday I was thinking

00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:05.720
as I was sitting on my desk,

00:28:05.720 --> 00:28:09.800
this is the way, walk ye in it.

00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:12.120
From Isaiah 30 and verse 21.

00:28:12.120 --> 00:28:13.360
I was beginning to meditate upon that.

00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:15.520
Aren't you thankful that God knows the way?

00:28:17.160 --> 00:28:19.760
Aren't you thankful that God will tell you the way?

00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:22.160
Amen?

00:28:22.160 --> 00:28:23.280
I mean, praise the Lord.

00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:24.920
Have you ever been lost and you just needed

00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:27.120
somebody to tell you the way?

00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:28.040
How do I get out?

00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:29.320
How do I find my...

00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:31.720
And you want somebody to give you the truth,

00:28:31.720 --> 00:28:33.200
somebody that knows.

00:28:33.200 --> 00:28:35.800
And we have the God of the universe

00:28:35.800 --> 00:28:37.320
who knows everything.

00:28:37.320 --> 00:28:39.119
Who knows you and knows me

00:28:39.119 --> 00:28:41.720
and he knows the end from the beginning.

00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:43.840
And he gives us direction.

00:28:43.840 --> 00:28:45.400
He gives us answers.

00:28:45.400 --> 00:28:48.240
And there are times unfortunately in our lives

00:28:48.240 --> 00:28:52.600
where we're not content with the answer that God gives.

00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:53.740
And that's tragedy.

00:28:56.040 --> 00:28:58.880
Because we want what we want.

00:28:59.720 --> 00:29:02.080
It's a real danger for us in America

00:29:02.080 --> 00:29:03.200
because we're spoiled.

00:29:04.559 --> 00:29:05.440
We're spoiled.

00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:10.080
Burger King made the little catchphrase years ago,

00:29:10.080 --> 00:29:12.000
have it your way.

00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:14.840
Right?

00:29:16.520 --> 00:29:18.760
And that appealed to the American public.

00:29:18.760 --> 00:29:19.600
Why?

00:29:19.600 --> 00:29:21.840
Because we want it our way.

00:29:23.080 --> 00:29:23.980
It's what we want.

00:29:26.160 --> 00:29:27.480
We want it our way.

00:29:27.480 --> 00:29:30.280
Now we want God's stamp of approval on it,

00:29:30.280 --> 00:29:31.600
but we want it our way.

00:29:33.000 --> 00:29:34.460
And here's what happens.

00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:39.960
Paul says, I have assaulted the Lord thrice,

00:29:39.960 --> 00:29:44.160
that it might depart from me and he, the Lord.

00:29:46.080 --> 00:29:48.280
The Lord said unto me,

00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:54.520
my grace is sufficient for thee.

00:29:54.520 --> 00:30:00.520
For my strength is made perfect in weakness.

00:30:00.520 --> 00:30:10.720
See, I believe that God could have removed the thorn.

00:30:10.720 --> 00:30:14.200
I believe that.

00:30:14.200 --> 00:30:21.060
Just like I believe that God could still the storm.

00:30:21.060 --> 00:30:26.040
But I believe that God chose to do something greater in this passage of Scripture and He

00:30:26.040 --> 00:30:33.700
chose to give us a principle that was so important for us to know.

00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:39.780
And here's the principle, God's grace is sufficient.

00:30:39.780 --> 00:30:47.500
We find that here as He besought the Lord that He was understanding that God was able.

00:30:47.500 --> 00:30:57.660
But God said, I'm going to do something for you that's so important for you to understand.

00:30:57.660 --> 00:31:07.340
My grace, that enablement is sufficient for thee.

00:31:07.340 --> 00:31:13.580
He tells them this, for my strength is made perfect in weakness.

00:31:13.580 --> 00:31:18.600
We're going to look entirely next week at the latter part of these two verses and preach

00:31:18.600 --> 00:31:25.780
a message on how Paul really, what his response is and his embracing of the truth, the answer

00:31:25.780 --> 00:31:27.780
that God gave.

00:31:27.780 --> 00:31:32.420
But I want you just for a moment to focus here on God's grace.

00:31:32.420 --> 00:31:35.900
We've preached about it all year, God's grace is sufficient.

00:31:35.900 --> 00:31:38.900
God's grace is sufficient and it is.

00:31:38.900 --> 00:31:44.460
I said this on the very first Sunday of this year when I preached to open up this theme,

00:31:44.460 --> 00:31:48.460
that God did not say my grace will be sufficient.

00:31:48.460 --> 00:31:52.300
He did not say that my grace was sufficient.

00:31:52.300 --> 00:31:55.540
He said that my grace is sufficient.

00:31:55.540 --> 00:31:57.380
It's present tense.

00:31:57.380 --> 00:32:04.220
It's understanding that in the moment, whatever moment we're in, that God's grace is sufficient.

00:32:04.220 --> 00:32:08.220
And this is so powerful and it's so helpful for us as God's people, why?

00:32:08.220 --> 00:32:11.740
Because we understand that God's enabling.

00:32:11.740 --> 00:32:14.900
This grace here is not talking about God's saving grace.

00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:16.580
Paul's already a man that's saved.

00:32:16.580 --> 00:32:19.560
We're not talking about, for by grace are you saved through faith, although I'm thankful

00:32:19.560 --> 00:32:21.740
for the saving grace of God.

00:32:21.740 --> 00:32:27.060
This is the enabling, that service grace, the enablement that God would give to the

00:32:27.060 --> 00:32:28.340
apostle Paul.

00:32:28.340 --> 00:32:30.500
And can I tell you this?

00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:38.060
God's grace is sufficient for you and it is sufficient for me.

00:32:38.900 --> 00:32:41.460
We find that there's an unending supply of God's grace.

00:32:41.460 --> 00:32:42.580
It's not going to run out.

00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:44.140
It's not going to run dry.

00:32:44.140 --> 00:32:45.860
His grace is sufficient.

00:32:45.860 --> 00:32:50.980
And you say, sometimes we play this game and we say, I don't know if I could ever deal

00:32:50.980 --> 00:32:55.380
with, and we get into this hypothetical mode of what happens if this were to come in my

00:32:55.380 --> 00:32:57.500
life or if this were to come in my life.

00:32:57.500 --> 00:32:59.620
And I just, it would just destroy me.

00:32:59.620 --> 00:33:06.300
And the problem with that kind of thinking is that God's grace is sufficient in the moment.

00:33:06.300 --> 00:33:13.180
Not in advance, not in the hypothetical, when in the moment you find that God's grace

00:33:13.180 --> 00:33:16.820
is sufficient.

00:33:16.820 --> 00:33:21.580
And this morning, when we look at the answer that the apostle Paul received, I do not think

00:33:21.580 --> 00:33:25.620
it was the answer that he was expecting, the answer that he was looking for, but it was

00:33:25.620 --> 00:33:28.300
the answer that he needed.

00:33:28.300 --> 00:33:29.860
And it's the answer that we need.

00:33:29.860 --> 00:33:32.100
God's grace is sufficient.

00:33:32.100 --> 00:33:36.280
And we find here this morning that we must ask ourselves this question, and it will lead

00:33:36.280 --> 00:33:38.180
into the message for next week.

00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:41.180
Will we, will you trust God?

00:33:41.180 --> 00:33:42.740
Will you believe God?

00:33:42.740 --> 00:33:46.820
Will you believe that God's grace is sufficient?

00:33:46.820 --> 00:33:50.780
Will you believe in the midst of your storm, in the midst of the turmoil, in the midst

00:33:50.780 --> 00:33:58.660
of all that's going on, will you believe, will you embrace the very truth that God's

00:33:58.660 --> 00:34:04.820
grace is sufficient?

00:34:04.820 --> 00:34:08.300
Because Paul, he embraces it.

00:34:08.300 --> 00:34:09.300
He embraces it.

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:12.660
He believes God.

00:34:12.660 --> 00:34:14.700
And we too must believe God.

00:34:14.700 --> 00:34:17.740
You say, but you don't understand the storm.

00:34:17.740 --> 00:34:19.580
You don't understand God.

00:34:19.580 --> 00:34:24.700
Listen, the storms will vary in their intensity.

00:34:24.700 --> 00:34:29.180
The storms will vary in their duration.

00:34:29.180 --> 00:34:35.700
But one thing that we must acknowledge is that God's grace is sufficient, regardless

00:34:35.700 --> 00:34:40.900
of the intensity of the storm, regardless of the duration of the storm, God's grace

00:34:40.900 --> 00:34:43.860
is sufficient.

00:34:43.860 --> 00:34:47.340
And it's so powerful for us.

00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:55.380
And in the text of Scripture, God gave to Paul revelations, visions.

00:34:55.380 --> 00:34:59.140
He gave him a thorn, and he gave him an answer.

00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:04.540
This morning, we see that God's grace is sufficient, it's so vital, it's so important for us to

00:35:04.540 --> 00:35:05.540
embrace that.

00:35:05.540 --> 00:35:11.860
But as we make that priority on humility, as we find that Paul says, lest I should be

00:35:11.860 --> 00:35:21.780
exalted above measure, can I ask you this morning, are you battling pride?

00:35:21.780 --> 00:35:29.220
Some things that cause you to be prideful, lifted up, not trusting God like we should.

00:35:29.220 --> 00:35:34.380
I've referenced already the truth of James when he says that God resisteth the proud

00:35:34.380 --> 00:35:35.740
but giveth grace to the humble.

00:35:35.740 --> 00:35:40.060
I want to remind you of what Paul said to the believers in Corinth in 1 Corinthians

00:35:40.060 --> 00:35:45.180
chapter 4 as he speaks to them about this, about a foundational principle that will

00:35:45.180 --> 00:35:49.780
help them in their approach to having humility.

00:35:49.780 --> 00:35:54.620
He says in verse 6 of 1 Corinthians 4, and these things, brethren, I have in a figure

00:35:54.620 --> 00:36:01.820
transferred to myself and to Apollos for your sakes, that you might learn in us not to think

00:36:01.820 --> 00:36:10.020
of men above that which is written, that no one of you be puffed up for one against another.

00:36:10.580 --> 00:36:15.780
And then Paul asks these questions, for who maketh thee to differ from another?

00:36:15.780 --> 00:36:19.460
In just a little while in the book of 1 Corinthians, Paul's going to begin to deal with spiritual

00:36:19.460 --> 00:36:20.460
gifts.

00:36:20.460 --> 00:36:25.380
And the Holy Spirit giveth to every man severally as he will.

00:36:25.380 --> 00:36:28.260
Who maketh thee to differ from another?

00:36:28.260 --> 00:36:32.620
God gave you a specific gift, but he gave somebody else a specific gift, but the reality

00:36:32.620 --> 00:36:34.440
is that God gave it.

00:36:34.440 --> 00:36:41.080
He says as he continues in verse number 7, what hast thou that thou didst not receive?

00:36:41.080 --> 00:36:45.320
Because everything that we have is from the hand of God.

00:36:45.320 --> 00:36:50.560
So if we understand the foundational principle, what is there to be prideful about?

00:36:50.560 --> 00:36:56.880
Because all that I am and all that I have is the result of God and His favor.

00:36:56.880 --> 00:37:03.640
Notice with me as we close this morning in 1 Peter, in 1 Peter chapter number 5, Peter

00:37:03.840 --> 00:37:09.120
is writing to these that are facing great persecution, they're scattered abroad, all

00:37:09.120 --> 00:37:10.280
that's going on.

00:37:10.280 --> 00:37:15.520
As he comes to the end of the epistle, he writes to specifically, the attention here

00:37:15.520 --> 00:37:18.560
turns to the church leaders.

00:37:18.560 --> 00:37:24.720
He says, the elders which are among you I exhort, who am also an elder.

00:37:24.720 --> 00:37:31.720
So we find that Peter is giving this instruction, he gives a great warning in the text about

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:39.000
our enemy who's walking about, not just to trip up, but to devour.

00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:44.200
But we find in the midst of this passage, I want you to notice verses 5 and 6 and what

00:37:44.200 --> 00:37:46.280
Peter says here.

00:37:46.280 --> 00:37:50.720
He says this, likewise ye younger, submit yourselves unto the elder, yea, all of you

00:37:50.720 --> 00:37:53.640
be subject one to another.

00:37:53.640 --> 00:38:00.640
And then he says this, and be clothed with humility.

00:38:00.760 --> 00:38:07.200
For God resisteth the proud and giveth grace to the humble.

00:38:07.200 --> 00:38:14.400
Humble yourselves therefore unto the mighty hand of God that He may exalt you in due time.

00:38:14.400 --> 00:38:21.040
As we notice in verse 5, he makes the statement to be clothed with humility.

00:38:21.040 --> 00:38:22.040
To be clothed with humility.

00:38:22.040 --> 00:38:27.920
That it would be evidenced, just like you can see someone's clothing, that we would

00:38:27.920 --> 00:38:31.380
be clothed in humility.

00:38:31.380 --> 00:38:34.360
Do you know what a pride person looks like and acts like?

00:38:34.360 --> 00:38:36.840
Can you pick them out?

00:38:36.840 --> 00:38:38.320
You can, right?

00:38:38.320 --> 00:38:44.400
Pride is easily detectable in others, not always in ourselves.

00:38:44.400 --> 00:38:45.400
Am I right?

00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:50.440
But he says, be clothed with humility.

00:38:50.440 --> 00:38:53.400
Be clothed with humility.

00:38:53.400 --> 00:38:57.000
And then he goes on and he talks about, as we mentioned from James, that God resisteth

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:58.720
the proud, giveth grace to the humble.

00:38:58.720 --> 00:39:01.280
I don't want God resisting me.

00:39:01.280 --> 00:39:02.520
I want God's favor.

00:39:02.520 --> 00:39:03.720
I want His grace.

00:39:03.720 --> 00:39:06.160
I want His enabling.

00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:11.440
And then he makes the statement, humble yourselves.

00:39:11.440 --> 00:39:12.980
Humble yourselves.

00:39:12.980 --> 00:39:21.239
If we choose not to take and follow that admonition, God will humble you.

00:39:21.239 --> 00:39:22.239
And He is able.

00:39:22.880 --> 00:39:23.880
And can I say this?

00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:33.480
It'd be far better for every single one of us that we humble ourselves than that God

00:39:33.480 --> 00:39:36.760
would humble us.

00:39:36.760 --> 00:39:41.920
I said in the beginning, but if we can see God in His rightful place, if we see Him high,

00:39:41.920 --> 00:39:47.160
holy, and lifted up, it'll help us to be humble.

00:39:47.160 --> 00:39:52.480
We stand in awe of Him and say, what am I?

00:39:52.480 --> 00:39:53.480
I'm undeserving.

00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:55.960
Aren't you undeserving?

00:39:55.960 --> 00:39:58.960
I don't deserve to go to heaven.

00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:02.520
but God's grace.

00:40:02.520 --> 00:40:04.020
Can I tell you that sometimes

00:40:04.020 --> 00:40:05.800
we have a right position

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:07.340
doctrinally?

00:40:07.340 --> 00:40:08.800
The truth?

00:40:08.800 --> 00:40:13.000
If we're not careful, it can make us prideful.

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:14.620
And having the truth can make us

00:40:14.620 --> 00:40:18.160
look down upon others that don't have the truth.

00:40:18.160 --> 00:40:19.860
It can cause us in our witnessing

00:40:19.860 --> 00:40:21.380
to be prideful,

00:40:21.380 --> 00:40:22.820
to be arrogant.

00:40:22.820 --> 00:40:25.120
But knowing the truth doesn't make us better,

00:40:25.120 --> 00:40:28.040
it makes us simply responsible.

00:40:28.040 --> 00:40:31.260
We are debtors, as Paul says in Romans 1.

00:40:31.260 --> 00:40:32.580
God's given us the truth,

00:40:32.580 --> 00:40:34.800
and it's not so that we can look down at others,

00:40:34.800 --> 00:40:36.680
it's so that we can give them...

00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:40.980
Listen, Satan, if we believe all of the Bible,

00:40:40.980 --> 00:40:42.560
the God of this world hath blinded the minds

00:40:42.560 --> 00:40:44.000
of them which believe not,

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:45.400
lest the light of the glorious Gospel

00:40:45.400 --> 00:40:47.280
should shine unto them.

00:40:47.280 --> 00:40:49.640
And the reality is that it doesn't make us better,

00:40:49.640 --> 00:40:52.760
it makes us responsible.

00:40:52.760 --> 00:40:54.160
That there are people that are lost

00:40:54.160 --> 00:40:55.180
just like I was lost,

00:40:55.180 --> 00:40:57.640
just like you were lost.

00:40:57.640 --> 00:41:00.320
They don't need some pride, arrogant person

00:41:00.320 --> 00:41:03.200
to come in their pride of I have the truth.

00:41:03.200 --> 00:41:06.560
No, they need somebody that's clothed in humility,

00:41:06.560 --> 00:41:09.000
that's carrying the truth of God's Word

00:41:09.000 --> 00:41:12.360
to love them to Jesus.

00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:16.240
That's what they need.

00:41:16.240 --> 00:41:19.040
Paul says there needs to be a priority on humility.

00:41:19.040 --> 00:41:22.280
He was given a vision, visions really.

00:41:22.280 --> 00:41:23.440
He was given a thorn,

00:41:23.440 --> 00:41:25.080
and he was given an answer.

00:41:25.080 --> 00:41:26.400
I'm thankful this morning

00:41:27.880 --> 00:41:29.880
that he was given all of this truth

00:41:29.880 --> 00:41:31.640
that can help us.

00:41:31.640 --> 00:41:33.560
But I hope that as we take away this morning,

00:41:33.560 --> 00:41:36.280
we say, lest I should be exalted above measure.

00:41:37.840 --> 00:41:40.480
What is it gonna take in your life to keep us humble?

00:41:42.280 --> 00:41:45.920
Will you humble yourself under the mighty hand of God?

00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:46.760
Let's pray.

00:41:46.760 --> 00:41:47.680
Father, we love you.

00:41:47.680 --> 00:41:48.920
We thank you for loving us.

00:41:48.920 --> 00:41:50.440
We thank you for your Word.

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:54.780
And God, I pray that you would help us to walk

00:41:54.780 --> 00:41:55.860
in humility.

00:41:57.100 --> 00:41:59.220
Lord, we believe that you said

00:42:00.700 --> 00:42:02.700
twice that you resist the proud.

00:42:06.620 --> 00:42:11.620
Help us like Paul to place a priority on humility.

00:42:13.020 --> 00:42:14.820
Father, I pray that if there's one that's here

00:42:14.820 --> 00:42:16.020
that's not saved,

00:42:17.580 --> 00:42:19.500
I pray they would humble themselves.

00:42:21.460 --> 00:42:22.980
Come, let us take a Bible and show them

00:42:22.980 --> 00:42:25.620
how they can know for sure that heaven is their home.

00:42:28.340 --> 00:42:30.500
Father, if there's some that are dealing with pride

00:42:30.500 --> 00:42:33.860
at whatever measure, whatever level it might be,

00:42:33.860 --> 00:42:37.340
would you help us this morning to humble ourselves?

00:42:37.340 --> 00:42:40.660
Would you help us to be clothed in humility?

00:42:41.700 --> 00:42:44.820
As we think about the example of our Lord and Savior

00:42:44.820 --> 00:42:47.020
who humbled himself

00:42:47.980 --> 00:42:50.140
and became obedient unto death,

00:42:50.140 --> 00:42:51.820
even the death of the cross,

00:42:53.580 --> 00:42:56.100
Lord, you are God.

00:42:56.100 --> 00:42:58.100
You left the throne of heaven,

00:42:58.100 --> 00:43:02.700
the glory to come to this sin-cursed world to die for us,

00:43:03.740 --> 00:43:05.700
to rise.

00:43:05.700 --> 00:43:07.780
Leave us an example

00:43:08.700 --> 00:43:12.220
and help us to be clothed in humility.

00:43:12.220 --> 00:43:14.060
Would you work in these moments of invitation

00:43:14.060 --> 00:43:15.720
as only you can?

00:43:15.720 --> 00:43:16.740
We'll give you the honor and glory

00:43:16.740 --> 00:43:17.860
for every decision that's made.

00:43:17.860 --> 00:43:19.660
For it's in Christ's name we pray.

00:43:19.660 --> 00:43:20.540
Would you stand with me?

00:43:20.540 --> 00:43:22.500
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

00:43:22.940 --> 00:43:25.100
Kimberly's gonna play quietly on the piano.

00:43:25.100 --> 00:43:26.580
If you're not sure of heaven,

